            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 32136,
            "text": "[{\"thread_number\":0,\"last_query_datetime\":\"2026-05-29T12:25:17.955282\",\"mode\":\"copilot\",\"context_uuid\":\"e7ebf033-1417-4a4e-919b-bb666c83f6f8\",\"uuid\":\"9971c10b-7504-4172-9d90-d441399f1775\",\"frontend_uuid\":\"5d7ad2fd-f485-4e77-804f-334bec48bb00\",\"frontend_context_uuid\":\"4d03fcba-83bf-46fe-b336-5631c9c2be65\",\"slug\":\"9971c10b-7504-4172-9d90-d441399f1775\",\"title\":\"What is quantum computing?\",\"query_str\":\"What is quantum computing?\",\"first_answer\":\"{\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Quantum computing is a type of computing that uses qubits instead of ordinary bits, applying quantum mechanics to process information in ways classical computers cannot.  Unlike a normal bit, which is either 0 or 1, a qubit can be 0, 1, or a combination of both through superposition, and qubits can also be linked through entanglement.\\\\nClassical computers solve problems by manipulating bits step...\\\"}\",\"answer_preview\":\"Quantum computing is a type of computing that uses qubits instead of ordinary bits, applying quantum mechanics to process information in ways classical computers cannot.  Unlike a normal bit, which is either 0 or 1, a qubit can be 0, 1, or a combination of both through superposition, and qubits can also be linked through entanglement.\\nClassical computers solve problems by manipulating bits step...\",\"thread_access\":1,\"has_next_page\":true,\"status\":\"COMPLETED\",\"display_model\":\"gpt54_thinking\",\"expiry_time\":null,\"source\":\"default\",\"source_metadata\":null,\"thread_status\":\"completed\",\"thread_status_summary\":null,\"thread_status_summary_enum\":null,\"locked_reason\":null,\"wake_at\":null,\"crons\":null,\"stream_created_at\":null,\"persona_id\":null,\"query_source\":null,\"dream_mode\":null,\"unread\":true,\"query_count\":1,\"search_focus\":\"internet\",\"sources\":[\"web\"],\"featured_images\":[],\"read_write_token\":\"0856a626-553b-46c5-941e-675c7135ffcc\",\"total_threads\":99,\"social_info\":{\"view_count\":0,\"fork_count\":0,\"like_count\":0,\"user_likes\":false},\"assets\":[],\"num_assets\":0,\"attachments\":[]},{\"thread_number\":1,\"last_query_datetime\":\"2026-05-29T12:02:14.519975\",\"mode\":\"copilot\",\"context_uuid\":\"3059fb29-5916-4d19-8de5-6c58bddcc4ad\",\"uuid\":\"203cfbd4-f877-487f-b0eb-37880d94c0c3\",\"frontend_uuid\":\"683e37e5-5739-408b-80d1-1b6fd3aefc6f\",\"frontend_context_uuid\":\"e5235520-a272-4467-b211-873dad92cc5b\",\"slug\":\"203cfbd4-f877-487f-b0eb-37880d94c0c3\",\"title\":\"Analyze CRISPR technology future\",\"query_str\":\"Analyze CRISPR technology future\",\"first_answer\":\"{\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Here's the CRISPR Technology Future Analysis report. It covers the full landscape across medicine, agriculture, and technology — here are the headline findings:\\\\nClinical momentum: As of 2026, over 250 CRISPR clinical trials are tracked globally, with Casgevy (the first approved CRISPR medicine) treating patients across 50+ sites worldwide. The historic milestone of 2025 was the world's first...\\\"}\",\"answer_preview\":\"Here's the CRISPR Technology Future Analysis report. It covers the full landscape across medicine, agriculture, and technology — here are the headline findings:\\nClinical momentum: As of 2026, over 250 CRISPR clinical trials are tracked globally, with Casgevy (the first approved CRISPR medicine) treating patients across 50+ sites worldwide. The historic milestone of 2025 was the world's first...\",\"thread_access\":1,\"has_next_page\":true,\"status\":\"COMPLETED\",\"display_model\":\"pplx_alpha\",\"expiry_time\":null,\"source\":\"default\",\"source_metadata\":null,\"thread_status\":\"completed\",\"thread_status_summary\":null,\"thread_status_summary_enum\":null,\"locked_reason\":null,\"wake_at\":null,\"crons\":null,\"stream_created_at\":null,\"persona_id\":null,\"query_source\":null,\"dream_mode\":null,\"unread\":true,\"query_count\":1,\"search_focus\":\"internet\",\"sources\":[\"web\"],\"featured_images\":[],\"read_write_token\":\"f4a52279-0d0f-4b98-ae24-96f5b5ab49bb\",\"total_threads\":99,\"social_info\":{\"view_count\":0,\"fork_count\":0,\"like_count\":0,\"user_likes\":false},\"assets\":[],\"num_assets\":0,\"attachments\":[]},{\"thread_number\":2,\"last_query_datetime\":\"2026-05-29T11:59:09.941583\",\"mode\":\"copilot\",\"context_uuid\":\"8880faa8-ae4e-4471-ac22-ad1304c667d4\",\"uuid\":\"d6b7f6b4-725d-4b26-82f0-0a1c66c9d635\",\"frontend_uuid\":\"bcd5799c-c451-440f-ab9f-bfd8ec628a4e\",\"frontend_context_uuid\":\"f43d856d-f428-48fe-9d3d-f503f39431dc\",\"slug\":\"d6b7f6b4-725d-4b26-82f0-0a1c66c9d635\",\"title\":\"What is rust programming language\",\"query_str\":\"What is rust programming language\",\"first_answer\":\"{\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Rust is a modern programming language designed for performance, reliability, and memory safety. It is especially known for preventing many bugs at compile time through its ownership and borrowing system, and it does not use a garbage collector.\\\\nRust is popular for systems programming, command-line tools, web services, embedded software, and other performance-sensitive applications. Its tooling...\\\"}\",\"answer_preview\":\"Rust is a modern programming language designed for performance, reliability, and memory safety. It is especially known for preventing many bugs at compile time through its ownership and borrowing system, and it does not use a garbage collector.\\nRust is popular for systems programming, command-line tools, web services, embedded software, and other performance-sensitive applications. Its tooling...\",\"thread_access\":1,\"has_next_page\":true,\"status\":\"COMPLETED\",\"display_model\":\"claude45sonnet\",\"expiry_time\":null,\"source\":\"default\",\"source_metadata\":null,\"thread_status\":\"completed\",\"thread_status_summary\":null,\"thread_status_summary_enum\":null,\"locked_reason\":null,\"wake_at\":null,\"crons\":null,\"stream_created_at\":null,\"persona_id\":null,\"query_source\":null,\"dream_mode\":null,\"unread\":true,\"query_count\":1,\"search_focus\":\"internet\",\"sources\":[\"web\"],\"featured_images\":[],\"read_write_token\":\"4260d4d9-078b-4bf7-ae7f-904f3036e3a7\",\"total_threads\":99,\"social_info\":{\"view_count\":0,\"fork_count\":0,\"like_count\":0,\"user_likes\":false},\"assets\":[],\"num_assets\":0,\"attachments\":[]},{\"thread_number\":3,\"last_query_datetime\":\"2026-05-29T11:58:44.983455\",\"mode\":\"copilot\",\"context_uuid\":\"6a00c168-b24a-495c-adc0-041833169d33\",\"uuid\":\"243c52f4-9774-4d00-9b60-d3a3e5f5294c\",\"frontend_uuid\":\"2d677e49-0f89-4ee4-941d-0d37fd5dfdaa\",\"frontend_context_uuid\":\"e7fe1737-7c04-4a96-b8b7-355fef43348f\",\"slug\":\"243c52f4-9774-4d00-9b60-d3a3e5f5294c\",\"title\":\"Prove sqrt(2) is irrational\",\"query_str\":\"Prove sqrt(2) is irrational\",\"first_answer\":\"{\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Assume \\\\\\\\sqrt{2} is rational, so \\\\\\\\sqrt{2}=\\\\\\\\frac{a}{b} for integers a,b with no common factor and b\\\\\\\\neq 0. Squaring gives 2=\\\\\\\\frac{a^2}{b^2}, so a^2=2b^2, which means a^2 is even, and therefore a must be even.\\\\n\\\\nSo write a=2k for some integer k. Substituting back gives (2k)^2=2b^2, hence 4k^2=2b^2, so b^2=2k^2; thus b^2 is even, and therefore b is even too.\\\\n\\\\nBut now both a and b are even, so they...\\\"}\",\"answer_preview\":\"Assume \\\\sqrt{2} is rational, so \\\\sqrt{2}=\\\\frac{a}{b} for integers a,b with no common factor and b\\\\neq 0. Squaring gives 2=\\\\frac{a^2}{b^2}, so a^2=2b^2, which means a^2 is even, and therefore a must be even.\\n\\nSo write a=2k for some integer k. Substituting back gives (2k)^2=2b^2, hence 4k^2=2b^2, so b^2=2k^2; thus b^2 is even, and therefore b is even too.\\n\\nBut now both a and b are even, so they...\",\"thread_access\":1,\"has_next_page\":true,\"status\":\"COMPLETED\",\"display_model\":\"o3mini\",\"expiry_time\":null,\"source\":\"default\",\"source_metadata\":null,\"thread_status\":\"completed\",\"thread_status_summary\":null,\"thread_status_summary_enum\":null,\"locke